# The Great Divergence

## Diocletian Caesar Augustus
- Reign: 1037–1058 AUC (284–305 CE)
- Status: Divergence Point
- Notes:
  - In real history:
    - Divided the Empire into East and West
  - In Eternal Empire timeline:
    - Rejects permanent division
    - Creates the Imperial Provincial Administrative System
    - Modernizes taxation, logistics, military command, and civil administration
    - Prevents collapse of centralized imperial authority
  - Considered the "Second Founder of Rome"

---

## Constantine the Great
- Reign: 1059–1090 AUC (306–337 CE)
- Notes:
  - Christianity tolerated but never dominates the empire
  - Hellenism remains the state faith
  - Establishes Nova Roma (Constantinople) as secondary capital

